Create empty repo in git and add them as remote to your existing local repo by
git remote add origin <URL>

Then you can push changes to master in github from the origin in the local by
git push orgin master

Pull the changes which are on github but not in your local system by
git pull origin <branch you want to pull> 

Fork -  Make a copy of that repo in your own profile
Clone - Downloading the repo along with history of commits to our pc
Branches -  Creating a branch from the node
